2pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The Housing act 2004 section 225</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">,  amends</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> the above S 87 power by specifically  including addressing the accommodation needs for gypsies and travellers. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/schedule/15/paragraph/47"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2004/34/schedule/15/paragraph/47</span></a></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">The government’s “planning policy for  travellers’ sites” (PPTS) </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">states that all local planning authorities should have in place a five year supply of land for Travellers’ sites, based on robust evidence of need. Therefore there must be an effective process </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">in  place</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">,  in order for this assessed accommodation need to carried out and to be met. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">The PPTS states that local planning authorities should comply with the policy by March 2013. Six months later there is evidence of a </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">countrywide  failure</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> by  local authorities to include to Travellers accommodation needs in Local Plan..</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">We believe that what is needed is a duty to provide or facilitate the provision of sites. It was the existence of that duty (contained within the Caravan Sites Act 1968) between 1970 and 1994 that brought about the existence of virtually all the local authority Gypsy and Traveller sites that currently exist</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">We note that the UN Special Rapporteur on Housing, following her recent visit to the UK, stated</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">: </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">In closing, let me also mention that during my visit I have also received multiple testimonies on the shortage of sufficient, adequate and safe sites for Gypsy and Traveller communities across the United Kingdom, many of whom feel this is part of the stigma and discrimination they regularly face from Governments and society as a whole.  </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Despite multiple efforts and policies put in place to address this situation, it is fair to say that leaving local authorities to make their own decision with no accountability and national process to reconcile the Gypsy and Traveller settled communities remains a source of concern.</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">[</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">our</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> emphasis].</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">We  therefore</span><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt"> oppose the proposal to remove Clause 21 and request that it is withdrawn. </span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Gill Sans MT'; font-size:12pt">16 September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>